
NAME

pyselenium - productive Web UI testing

Test webapps lean in any browser with Selenium and Python

SETUP

pick 1 of 3 choices: Cygwin, Windows, Linux RH/Centos

Setup on Cygwin: (just do it - the best unix/mac like productive choice on Windows)

------------------

1. download Cygwin:
http://cygwin.com/setup-x86_64.exe

2. run command in dos cmd window:
setup-x86_64.exe -q -P nc,wget,vim,git,subversion,openssh,python3

3. prefix Windows system PATH with:
c:\cygwin64\bin;

4. Run command in Cygwin terminal:
cd; git clone http://irepo.eur.ad.sag/scm/~dkrukov/pyselenium.git && cd pyselenium
./install_pyse_cygwin

------------------

Setup on Windows native (not as optimal as with Cygwin):

------------------

1. install [python 3.5+](https://www.python.org/downloads)

2. install selenium module using command:
python -m pip install selenium==3.5.0

3. prepend system env PATH variable with the following:

%HOMEDRIVE%%HOMEPATH%\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python36-32\Scripts\;%HOMEDRIVE%%HOMEPATH%\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python36-32\;c:\cygwin64\bin;

Note: adjust PATH elements above for your version of python

4. add PYTHONPATH=src system env variable

5. ensure git package is installed

6. git clone http://irepo.eur.ad.sag/scm/~dkrukov/pyselenium.git

------------------

Setup on Linux RH/Centos:

------------------

1. ensure git package is installed
2. Run command:
cd; git clone http://irepo.eur.ad.sag/scm/~dkrukov/pyselenium.git && cd pyselenium
./install_pyse_rh

------------------

On any platform - Install browsers support and optional hub (to run tests like on remote hub):

------------------

1. install ie, firefox, chrome, edge browsers as needed

2. Install browsers' drivers and selenium hub using command:

./hub install

3. Optional - you may also launch hub on your local for test purposes:
   to run Selenium hub use one of these commands:

./hub		#starts hub and node
./hub hub	#starts just hub
./hub node	#starts just node which points to local hub
./hub node host:port	#starts just node, which points remote host:port hub; standard port is 4444

4. if jenkins is needed, start it like this (change <slavename> appropriately)
wget http://rdvmden113:8080/jenkins/jnlpJars/slave.jar -O- > slave.jar
java -jar slave.jar -jnlpUrl http://rdvmden113:8080/jenkins/computer/<slavename>/slave-agent.jnlp

5. DEPRECATED: Some extras may be needed by legacy BVTs and tests (firefox46, jdk8, ant1.9):
scp optimize@rdvmden54:/opt/sag/downloads/*{46,8u102,1.9.7}* . #pass: optimize
install them with respective .exe or tar -xvf (ant)
start firefox and disable all updates, should be v46 (for legacy BAMSelenium UI tests)
add JAVA_HOME env var, add java and ant bin dirs to PATH, also add firefox install dir to PATH

-----------------

Optional: On a dedicated host(s) around, install hub and nodes(as needed to scale and cover variety of browsers):
-----------------
wget http://irepo.eur.ad.sag/users/dkrukov/repos/pyselenium/raw/hub && chmod 755 hub

   to run Selenium hub use one of these commands:

./hub		#starts hub and node
./hub hub	#starts just hub
./hub node	#starts just node which points to local hub
./hub node host:port	#starts just node, which points remote host:port hub; standard port is 4444

USAGE

run Demo for KPI Creation Gadget

cd ~pyselenium
export cfg="{'browser':'chrome'}" #this runs local on either chrome|firefox|edge|ie
#export cfg="{ 'remote':true, 'hub':'http://rdvmva91:4444/wd/hub','browser':'chrome'}" #this runs on hub on respective browser
python -u t/dbm/kpi_creation_demo.py


